# SERVER/PRODUCTION CONFIGURATION
# Use this when deploying to Railway/Render

# ==============================================================================
# RAILWAY ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES GUIDE
# ==============================================================================
#
# AUTO-PROVIDED BY RAILWAY (DO NOT SET MANUALLY):
# - DATABASE_URL: Railway automatically provides this when you add a PostgreSQL service
# - PORT: Railway automatically sets this (remix-serve will use it)
#
# YOU MUST SET THESE IN RAILWAY DASHBOARD:
# - SHOPIFY_API_KEY
# - SHOPIFY_API_SECRET
# - SHOPIFY_APP_URL (use your Railway domain: https://yourapp.up.railway.app)
# - SCOPES
# - AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID (if using S3)
# - AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY (if using S3)
# - AWS_REGION (if using S3)
# - S3_BUCKET_NAME (if using S3)
# - SHOP_CUSTOM_DOMAIN (optional)
# - CLARITY_ID (optional)
# - SHOPIFY_APP_HANDLE (required - your app's URL handle, e.g., "product-notes-for-staff")
# - IS_TEST_BILLING (set to "true" when testing with development stores)
# ==============================================================================

# Shopify App Configuration
SHOPIFY_API_KEY=759aead17dfbcb721121009dacc43ce2
SHOPIFY_API_SECRET=cd2a9a6a0e7e45d8bc113dea282bf821
